name: Fish and Vegetable Foil Packets
author: Jules921
summary: Cooking fish in foil is a fun, fast, kid-friendly way to get the kids to eat fish and veggies, adapted from Weight Watchers 5-Ingredient 15-Minute Recipes, Winter 2010.
ingredients: salt and ground black pepper to taste
⅓ cup torn fresh basil leaves
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Place 1/2 cup zucchini in the center of 1 piece of foil
Add 1/4 cup potatoes and 1 cod fillet; season with salt and pepper
Layer with 1/4 of the onion slices, 1/4 cup tomatoes, and 1/4 of the basil
Fold foil over vegetables, crimp edges to seal tightly, and place on a baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until vegetables are tender and fish flakes easily with a fork, about 20 minutes
